1
00:00:01,501 --> 00:00:03,044
[Jalil] <i>I already know the truth.</i>

2
00:00:03,128 --> 00:00:05,463
<i>Doctor Teresa and Marcus…</i>

3
00:00:05,547 --> 00:00:06,840
<i>They are my missing family.</i>

4
00:00:06,923 --> 00:00:08,925
[Felix] <i>Major Allan Espina</i>

5
00:00:09,009 --> 00:00:11,428
<i>and Jalil Abubakar are the same person.</i>

6
00:00:11,511 --> 00:00:13,179
My new Chief of Staff

7
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:16,016
will be General Manuel Carillo.

8
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:21,062
The group behind this destabilization

9
00:00:21,146 --> 00:00:23,106
is led by Hassan Wadi,

10
00:00:23,189 --> 00:00:26,568
who goes by the alias
Datu Rahman Abubakar.

11
00:00:26,651 --> 00:00:27,777
He's framing me!

12
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:29,320
Damn it!

13
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:32,699
[Datu Rahman] <i>He's carrying on</i>
<i>what his brother,</i>

14
00:00:32,782 --> 00:00:35,618
<i>Colonel Napoleon Marcelino, started.</i>

15
00:00:35,702 --> 00:00:37,954
He was the former leader

16
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,789
- of the syndicate!
- [gunshot]

17
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:43,042
[Jalil] <i>Father!</i>

18
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,464
- [Teresa] <i>Jamilah!</i>
- [Jalil] <i>Hurry up!</i>

19
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:49,841
[Jalil] <i>Hurry!</i>

20
00:00:49,924 --> 00:00:52,427
- [Teresa] <i>Time of death, 12:34.</i>
- [Jamilah screams]

21
00:00:52,510 --> 00:00:53,678
[Jamilah] <i>Father!</i>

22
00:00:53,762 --> 00:00:54,804
[Marcus] <i>Espina…</i>

23
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:56,681
He's Jalil Abubakar.

24
00:00:56,765 --> 00:00:58,058
[Usman] <i>He worked for Sir Mustapha.</i>

25
00:00:58,141 --> 00:01:00,894
[Marcus] <i>Why did Sir Mustapha</i>
<i>plant a spy in NLEA?</i>

26
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:04,230
[Usman] <i>Because they're looking</i>
<i>for the real traitor in NLEA.</i>

27
00:01:04,814 --> 00:01:05,732
‪[grunts]

28
00:01:05,815 --> 00:01:07,484
[Marcus] <i>We can't do anything</i>
<i>about that now.</i>

29
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:09,694
<i>It's our duty to arrest him, brother.</i>

30
00:01:10,236 --> 00:01:11,279
[Jalil] <i>Bro…</i>

31
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:12,572
Bro, please, grant me this.

32
00:01:12,655 --> 00:01:14,365
[Jalil] <i>I have to bury my father.</i>

33
00:01:14,449 --> 00:01:16,659
<i>Bro, I have to bury my father.</i>

34
00:01:16,743 --> 00:01:17,994
<i>When Sir Mustapha died,</i>

35
00:01:18,078 --> 00:01:21,498
<i>I knew my identity was at risk</i>
<i>of being exposed.</i>

36
00:01:21,581 --> 00:01:24,292
<i>But I had to finish</i>
<i>the mission he left behind.</i>

37
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:27,629
<i>I had to help you find</i>
<i>and arrest General Carillo.</i>

38
00:01:27,712 --> 00:01:31,216
It has been verified by Jalil Abubakar

39
00:01:31,299 --> 00:01:37,388
that Domingo is among
the traitors in our ranks!

40
00:01:37,472 --> 00:01:40,141
[Azuelo] <i>The mission before you</i>
<i>is to arrest</i>

41
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:43,186
<i>SPO4 Felix Domingo!</i>

42
00:01:43,269 --> 00:01:45,396
[Jalil] <i>Police Major Allan Espina</i>
<i>is not real.</i>

43
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,898
<i>But everything I showed you…</i>

44
00:01:46,981 --> 00:01:48,483
<i>All of it was real.</i>

45
00:01:48,566 --> 00:01:50,318
<i>I didn't just see you as a friend.</i>

46
00:01:50,401 --> 00:01:52,320
<i>I came to see you as my brother.</i>

47
00:01:55,907 --> 00:02:02,539
[mysterious theme music playing]

48
00:02:10,588 --> 00:02:12,006
Hold on, hold on!

49
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:14,092
Every single day, every single hour,

50
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:15,510
there's another bombshell.

51
00:02:15,593 --> 00:02:18,138
What's going on? Who's telling the truth?

52
00:02:18,221 --> 00:02:19,722
General Carillo says

53
00:02:19,806 --> 00:02:22,767
Datu Rahman is behind the destabilization.

54
00:02:22,851 --> 00:02:24,769
But Datu Rahman says

55
00:02:24,853 --> 00:02:27,230
it's General Carillo and his brother.

56
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:28,481
And now,

57
00:02:28,565 --> 00:02:31,109
Jalil Abubakar's name
has entered the picture.

58
00:02:31,192 --> 00:02:33,778
Get your stories straight.
Who's really telling the truth?

59
00:02:33,862 --> 00:02:35,446
We need the truth!

60
00:02:35,530 --> 00:02:37,699
Tell us what's really going on!

61
00:02:38,783 --> 00:02:40,410
They're trying to confuse us.

62
00:02:40,493 --> 00:02:42,579
<i>They're all saying different things</i>

63
00:02:42,662 --> 00:02:45,290
<i>so we won't know the truth!</i>

64
00:02:46,374 --> 00:02:48,167
<i>But they can't fool us anymore!</i>

65
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:53,381
<i>Because we already know</i>
<i>that whoever tells the truth</i>

66
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:55,758
<i>is the one they silence!</i>

67
00:02:55,842 --> 00:02:57,969
Just like Sir Mustapha before, right?

68
00:02:58,553 --> 00:02:59,804
And now

69
00:02:59,888 --> 00:03:01,890
Datu Rahman!

70
00:03:02,473 --> 00:03:04,559
<i>Does that mean…</i>

71
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:08,021
<i>he's the one telling the truth?</i>

72
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:10,481
THIS HAS GONE TOO FAR!
IT'S NOT FUNNY ANYMORE!

73
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:12,650
<i>Let's not lose hope.</i>

74
00:03:12,734 --> 00:03:15,278
<i>Let's not lose hope!</i>

75
00:03:15,361 --> 00:03:16,696
[in Arabic] <i>God willing.</i>

76
00:03:16,779 --> 00:03:17,822
[sobbing]

77
00:03:17,906 --> 00:03:21,367
<i>In the end, the truth will come out.</i>

78
00:03:21,451 --> 00:03:23,036
- THIS IS GETTING SERIOUS!
- DO SOMETHING, DON’T JUST STARE!

79
00:03:23,119 --> 00:03:24,078
[sighs]

80
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:25,705
- I can't believe all this.
- Yeah.

81
00:03:25,788 --> 00:03:27,749
But wait, Mama Loi.

82
00:03:27,832 --> 00:03:30,793
- When Ahmad Mustapha was still alive,
- Yes?

83
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:33,379
didn't he clear Jalil Abubakar's name?

84
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:35,632
- Yeah. Why?
- Right?

85
00:03:35,715 --> 00:03:38,968
Then why didn't he come forward back then?

86
00:03:39,552 --> 00:03:42,722
Maybe he just wasn't ready
for his close-up!

87
00:03:42,805 --> 00:03:43,932
Huh?

88
00:03:44,015 --> 00:03:45,558
I'm about to slap you with my foot.

89
00:03:45,642 --> 00:03:47,018
You're always joking, Mrena.

90
00:03:47,101 --> 00:03:48,436
This is serious.

91
00:03:48,519 --> 00:03:50,021
That's exactly it.

92
00:03:50,104 --> 00:03:53,858
He wasn't even wanted
by the authorities, right?

93
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:58,404
So why was he pretending
to be Major Allan Espina?

94
00:03:59,530 --> 00:04:02,242
- That's what's bothering me too.
- [sighs]

95
00:04:02,325 --> 00:04:04,619
There's no way he could've
gotten into the NLEA

96
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:06,246
- that easily.
- Yeah.

97
00:04:06,329 --> 00:04:08,414
Especially if he was using
a fake identity.

98
00:04:08,498 --> 00:04:09,540
[Ogie] Exactly.

99
00:04:09,624 --> 00:04:11,209
- So…
- [Ogie] Hmm?

100
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:12,919
Who let him in?

101
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:15,213
- Hey, it wasn't me!
- Really?

102
00:04:15,296 --> 00:04:17,966
Hey, I got fooled too!

103
00:04:18,049 --> 00:04:19,384
What if…

104
00:04:19,467 --> 00:04:20,468
it was Mrena?

105
00:04:20,551 --> 00:04:22,971
Hey! It wasn't me either!

106
00:04:23,054 --> 00:04:24,514
Then who?

107
00:04:24,597 --> 00:04:26,683
This is driving me crazy!

108
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,601
Who could it be?

109
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:31,521
[sirens wailing]

110
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:38,861
[suspenseful music playing]

111
00:05:02,093 --> 00:05:03,845
Tsk, tsk, tsk!

112
00:05:08,349 --> 00:05:10,018
[line ringing]

113
00:05:10,601 --> 00:05:12,145
[in English] Alpha to Base.

114
00:05:12,228 --> 00:05:14,022
- [in English] Target's missing.
- [radio static]

115
00:05:14,105 --> 00:05:15,815
Find him!

116
00:05:15,898 --> 00:05:18,943
Don't stop until you've captured

117
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:20,611
that traitor, Domingo!

118
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:27,452
General.

119
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:30,997
I can't go back to the NLEA.

120
00:05:31,581 --> 00:05:33,583
The NLEA and SID are after me.

121
00:05:34,417 --> 00:05:36,794
Go into hiding. Don't let them catch you.

122
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:40,631
Our plan isn't over yet.

123
00:05:43,176 --> 00:05:44,343
[in English] Okay.

124
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:47,597
I promise you

125
00:05:48,473 --> 00:05:51,434
you'll make it back to the NLEA.

126
00:05:52,643 --> 00:05:54,187
[in English] Copy, General.

127
00:05:55,354 --> 00:05:56,355
Thank you.

128
00:05:56,439 --> 00:06:01,069
[suspenseful music intensifies]

129
00:06:10,036 --> 00:06:11,245
[music stops]

130
00:06:11,829 --> 00:06:13,414
[Jalil in Arabic] In the name of Allah.

131
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:19,587
[melancholic music playing]

132
00:06:31,849 --> 00:06:33,351
[in Arabic] In the name of Allah.

133
00:06:34,143 --> 00:06:38,981
[melancholic music continues]

134
00:06:48,116 --> 00:06:49,075
[Jalil, in Arabic] <i>In the name of Allah.</i>

135
00:06:49,158 --> 00:06:51,953
[in Arabic] <i>In the name of Allah.</i>

136
00:06:52,036 --> 00:06:56,457
[melancholic music continues]

137
00:07:05,675 --> 00:07:07,093
[in Arabic] In the name of Allah.

138
00:07:23,234 --> 00:07:25,862
[music fades]

139
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:35,455
[morose music playing]

140
00:07:39,333 --> 00:07:40,543
[Jamilah sobbing]

141
00:07:46,507 --> 00:07:50,011
[Jamilah sobbing]

142
00:07:50,094 --> 00:07:53,556
[morose music continues]

143
00:07:54,223 --> 00:07:55,433
Jalil…

144
00:07:56,601 --> 00:08:01,230
[sobbing]

145
00:08:02,899 --> 00:08:09,405
[Jamilah whimpering]

146
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:18,414
Jalil…

147
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:23,503
[Jamilah whimpering]

148
00:08:24,086 --> 00:08:26,088
[crying]

149
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:35,223
[morose music continues]

150
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:49,695
[music turns dramatic]

151
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:11,926
[dramatic music continues]

152
00:09:13,219 --> 00:09:15,555
[Jamilah sobbing]

153
00:09:16,472 --> 00:09:19,016
[Marcus] You have the right
to remain silent.

154
00:09:19,100 --> 00:09:21,394
Anything you say can and will
be used against you

155
00:09:21,477 --> 00:09:23,646
in any Philippine court of law.

156
00:09:23,729 --> 00:09:24,564
‪[Jamilah sobs]

157
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:37,076
[somber music playing]

158
00:09:52,550 --> 00:09:53,884
Jalil!

159
00:09:54,885 --> 00:09:57,430
[sobbing]

160
00:10:01,934 --> 00:10:03,436
Please take care of yourself.

161
00:10:03,519 --> 00:10:05,354
Please, Jalil.

162
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:09,817
[Jamilah wailing]

163
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,110
[softly] Don't worry about me.

164
00:10:11,193 --> 00:10:13,029
Jalil!

165
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:29,253
[Jamilah sobbing]

166
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:11,128
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil…</i>

167
00:11:25,393 --> 00:11:27,311
[siren wails]

168
00:11:27,395 --> 00:11:32,024
[tense music playing]

169
00:11:44,954 --> 00:11:46,956
Our deepest condolences, sir.

170
00:11:47,039 --> 00:11:48,624
Condolences, sir.

171
00:11:48,707 --> 00:11:50,960
- [in English] Sorry for your loss, sir.
- [in English] Condolences, sir.

172
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:54,880
[gloomy music playing]

173
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:58,551
[Madrid] Who does this guy think he is?

174
00:11:58,634 --> 00:12:01,178
He's a fraud! What a bastard!

175
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:02,555
[men chuckle]

176
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:05,516
What?

177
00:12:06,225 --> 00:12:07,435
[Montes] Got a problem?

178
00:12:07,518 --> 00:12:11,814
[tense music playing]

179
00:12:17,945 --> 00:12:20,489
My condolences to your family,

180
00:12:21,574 --> 00:12:23,451
Jalil Abubakar.

181
00:12:23,534 --> 00:12:26,162
Why did you salute him?

182
00:12:26,245 --> 00:12:28,289
He's not a real police officer.

183
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,466
Go on. Lock him up.

184
00:13:09,413 --> 00:13:10,831
[door handle clanks]

185
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:13,250
[lock clicks]

186
00:13:19,089 --> 00:13:20,966
I will solve this case.

187
00:13:22,968 --> 00:13:24,762
I will clear your name, brother.

188
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:28,140
[stirring music playing]

189
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,892
[in Tausug] Thank you, brother.

190
00:13:31,143 --> 00:13:32,478
[in Tausug] Thank you.

191
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:35,564
Don't worry.

192
00:13:37,024 --> 00:13:38,567
You will get out of here.

193
00:13:38,651 --> 00:13:40,110
[in Arabic] God willing.

194
00:13:41,737 --> 00:13:42,613
[in Arabic] God willing.

195
00:13:46,575 --> 00:13:47,785
[Jalil exhales heavily]

196
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:51,789
[Villanueva] So you're saying

197
00:13:51,872 --> 00:13:55,709
you'll be taking custody
of Jalil Abubakar?

198
00:13:57,545 --> 00:13:59,380
[in English] Exactly.

199
00:13:59,463 --> 00:14:00,631
Don't worry.

200
00:14:00,714 --> 00:14:01,966
We'll take it from here.

201
00:14:06,011 --> 00:14:07,388
- [in English] Okay.
- [in English] Sir.

202
00:14:07,471 --> 00:14:11,642
[unsettling music playing]

203
00:14:25,781 --> 00:14:27,575
You know what to do.

204
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,418
‪[man coughs]

205
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:45,092
Valdez.

206
00:14:46,051 --> 00:14:47,386
Why are you geared up?

207
00:14:47,469 --> 00:14:49,179
None of your business.

208
00:14:50,055 --> 00:14:50,973
[scoffs]

209
00:14:51,056 --> 00:14:54,894
I was assigned to handle
Jalil Abubakar's transfer.

210
00:14:55,519 --> 00:14:56,520
What transfer?

211
00:14:56,604 --> 00:14:58,439
[Valdez] Didn't they tell you?

212
00:14:58,522 --> 00:15:01,525
I guess they think
you'll help him escape instead.

213
00:15:01,609 --> 00:15:03,903
Just like you did with Datu Rahman.

214
00:15:08,657 --> 00:15:14,830
- [unsettling music playing]
- [sighs]

215
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:17,082
Sir Usman, are you okay?

216
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:18,584
- What happened?
- [sighs]

217
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:20,961
- Jalil's being transferred.
- What?!

218
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:24,423
What's odd is that
he's being transported tonight.

219
00:15:24,506 --> 00:15:29,261
[tense music playing]

220
00:15:37,144 --> 00:15:38,604
[young Datu Rahman] <i>You two are so silly.</i>

221
00:15:38,687 --> 00:15:42,066
- Finish cleaning his wound.
- No! Ouch, Jamilah! [laughs]

222
00:15:42,149 --> 00:15:44,234
<i>- Ah! Ouch!</i>
- [young Datu Rahman] <i>There you go.</i>

223
00:15:44,318 --> 00:15:46,362
- [young Jalil laughing]
- [young Jamilah giggling]

224
00:15:46,445 --> 00:15:47,738
[young Jalil] <i>Jamilah…</i> [laughs]

225
00:15:47,821 --> 00:15:49,156
<i>Ah!</i>

226
00:15:49,239 --> 00:15:50,574
[Jamilah] <i>Jalil!</i>

227
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:56,163
[pensive music playing]

228
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,133
I'm just so happy because it's like…

229
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:13,305
it's been so long
since we had a meal together.

230
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:14,890
[sniffles]

231
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:18,018
Don't mind me. Go ahead.
Just continue eating.

232
00:16:19,561 --> 00:16:24,149
[pensive music continues]

233
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:47,881
[pensive music continues]

234
00:16:57,266 --> 00:17:00,185
[Jalil in Arabic] <i>O Allah,</i>
<i>I seek refuge in You</i>

235
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:04,064
<i>from anxiety and sorrow,</i>
<i>weakness and laziness,</i>

236
00:17:04,148 --> 00:17:06,316
<i>miserliness and cowardice,</i>

237
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:11,196
<i>the burden of debts,</i>
<i>and from being overpowered by men.</i>

238
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:15,617
[pensive music continues]

239
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:25,669
Jamilah.

240
00:17:25,753 --> 00:17:27,046
I'll head out now.

241
00:17:27,129 --> 00:17:28,839
Again, my condolences.

242
00:17:28,922 --> 00:17:30,340
Thank you.

243
00:17:32,968 --> 00:17:35,929
[Jamilah breathes deeply]

244
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:39,308
Jamilah!

245
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:41,435
You worked today?

246
00:17:42,019 --> 00:17:48,317
[somber music playing]

247
00:17:53,614 --> 00:17:54,907
[Jamilah breathes heavily]

248
00:17:54,990 --> 00:17:56,158
Doctor…

249
00:17:57,201 --> 00:17:58,660
- Mom?
- [Jamilah whimpers]

250
00:18:00,245 --> 00:18:01,705
Jamilah.

251
00:18:04,708 --> 00:18:06,001
[Jamilah sobbing]

252
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:11,256
[Jamilah] Doctor Teresa…

253
00:18:12,508 --> 00:18:16,178
This is the bandage with the blood…

254
00:18:17,179 --> 00:18:19,056
of Major Espina.

255
00:18:19,139 --> 00:18:21,892
[Jamilah crying]

256
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:25,104
Of Jalil.

257
00:18:28,649 --> 00:18:31,401
I'm sorry, Doctor Teresa.

258
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:36,657
I'm sorry for hiding it.

259
00:18:37,533 --> 00:18:42,871
I'm sorry, I had to protect
my brother's identity.

260
00:18:42,955 --> 00:18:44,414
- [Teresa] Huh?
- Yes.

261
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:47,126
What do you mean, Jamilah?

262
00:18:47,209 --> 00:18:48,460
[Jamilah sobbing]

263
00:18:49,044 --> 00:18:52,840
You wanted to take a DNA test for him.

264
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:56,510
Because you thought that he was your son.

265
00:18:56,593 --> 00:18:58,679
That he was Gabriel.

266
00:18:58,762 --> 00:19:02,599
[crying]

267
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:06,645
But there's no need to get a DNA test now

268
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:09,857
because you're correct.

269
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:14,903
[somber music continues]

270
00:19:16,488 --> 00:19:19,741
- Jalil is Gabriel.
- [dramatic sting]

271
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:23,203
[Jamilah] I'm sorry.

272
00:19:23,287 --> 00:19:28,292
[sobbing]

273
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:33,046
Jalil is Gabriel?

274
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:35,424
[stirring music playing]

275
00:19:35,507 --> 00:19:40,929
[Jamilah crying]

276
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:42,514
He's alive?

277
00:19:44,308 --> 00:19:45,726
Gabriel is alive?

278
00:19:51,982 --> 00:19:53,400
[Jamilah] He is.

279
00:19:53,483 --> 00:19:56,195
[stirring music continues]

280
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:58,739
[Jamilah and Teresa crying]

281
00:20:00,282 --> 00:20:04,578
My father got Jalil
when the ship exploded.

282
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,915
[Teresa crying]

283
00:20:07,998 --> 00:20:10,125
[Jamilah] When Jalil regained
his consciousness,

284
00:20:10,209 --> 00:20:12,461
he couldn't remember anything.

285
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:18,592
But Jalil slowly regained his memories.

286
00:20:19,259 --> 00:20:22,971
He knows that you're his real family.

287
00:20:23,805 --> 00:20:27,309
[crying continues]

288
00:20:29,186 --> 00:20:31,730
Why didn't he tell me right away?

289
00:20:31,813 --> 00:20:33,899
[music intensifies]

290
00:20:33,982 --> 00:20:35,901
He badly wanted to.

291
00:20:35,984 --> 00:20:38,487
He badly wanted to tell you.

292
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:39,780
Yes.

293
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:42,491
[Jamilah] But…

294
00:20:43,367 --> 00:20:46,703
General Carillo already framed him.

295
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:50,332
He didn't want you
to be associated with him.

296
00:20:50,415 --> 00:20:53,043
He just wanted to protect you.

297
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:58,006
[both crying]

298
00:20:59,007 --> 00:21:00,884
Gabriel…

299
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:04,972
[Jamilah] But now…

300
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:08,267
I no longer want to hide the truth.

301
00:21:10,811 --> 00:21:16,191
Especially now that Jalil's life
might be in danger.

302
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:26,410
[phone ringing]

303
00:21:26,493 --> 00:21:30,414
[Marcus sniffles]

304
00:21:30,497 --> 00:21:31,415
Buddy.

305
00:21:31,498 --> 00:21:34,543
Buddy… Buddy, they're going to kill Jalil.

306
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:36,420
‪-[dramatic sting]
‪-What?

307
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:39,756
[tense music playing]

308
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:41,800
What's going on? [sobs]

309
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:44,845
- It's Gabriel.
- [Jamilah] Huh?

310
00:21:46,221 --> 00:21:47,681
Brother Jalil…

311
00:21:49,516 --> 00:21:52,019
What happened to Gabriel, Marcus?!

312
00:21:54,771 --> 00:22:00,444
[suspenseful music playing]

313
00:22:10,454 --> 00:22:14,124
[inaudible chatter]

314
00:22:14,207 --> 00:22:15,625
[gun cocks]

315
00:22:17,002 --> 00:22:22,049
[suspenseful music continues]

316
00:22:47,157 --> 00:22:50,035
- [electronic whirring]
- [fire alarm blaring]

317
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:51,536
Why did the power go out?

318
00:22:53,121 --> 00:22:54,915
What happened? Is there a power outage?

319
00:22:54,998 --> 00:22:57,292
[fire alarm blaring continues]

320
00:22:57,375 --> 00:22:58,710
Let's move!

321
00:22:58,794 --> 00:23:02,631
[suspenseful music continues]

322
00:23:14,309 --> 00:23:15,936
[cop 1] Why is the fire alarm blaring?

323
00:23:16,019 --> 00:23:17,020
[cop 2] Is there a fire?

324
00:23:17,687 --> 00:23:18,897
What happened?

325
00:23:20,148 --> 00:23:22,234
- [coughs]
- Hey!

326
00:23:22,317 --> 00:23:26,238
[overlapping shouting, coughing]

327
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:31,952
My goodness! What's going on?

328
00:23:33,203 --> 00:23:34,955
- [Madrid coughing]
- I don't know!

329
00:23:42,003 --> 00:23:43,755
[groaning]

330
00:24:01,815 --> 00:24:02,816
[Jalil] Who are you?!

331
00:24:10,490 --> 00:24:11,616
Sabdani?

332
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:13,577
Jalil.

333
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:14,995
Usman!

334
00:24:15,996 --> 00:24:17,414
What's going on?

335
00:24:17,497 --> 00:24:20,167
Jalil, let's go!
They're going to kill you!

336
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:21,543
Come on!

337
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:25,547
[suspenseful music intensifies]

338
00:24:32,137 --> 00:24:34,306
[Montes] <i>You let a criminal escape again!</i>

339
00:24:34,389 --> 00:24:36,308
<i>All because you're both Muslims!</i>

340
00:24:36,391 --> 00:24:38,393
- Try and hurt him.
- Go on!

341
00:24:38,476 --> 00:24:39,769
I'll finish your mission.

342
00:24:39,853 --> 00:24:42,314
<i>I'll put an end to Carillo's wickedness.</i>

343
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:45,192
Tell me where you are,
so I can protect you!

344
00:24:45,275 --> 00:24:47,485
Dear God, watch over my sons.

345
00:24:48,445 --> 00:24:51,907
Those two are the real criminals,
and yet you call me the traitor?!

346
00:24:51,990 --> 00:24:56,453
The police are deeply compromised.

347
00:24:56,536 --> 00:24:58,747
[Marcus] <i>We will take down</i>
<i>General Carillo together.</i>

348
00:24:58,830 --> 00:25:00,248
<i>As partners.</i>

349
00:25:00,332 --> 00:25:01,708
<i>As comrades.</i>

350
00:25:01,791 --> 00:25:02,626
<i>As brothers.</i>
